-- #171: the bare-2^62 rejection must point AT the literal, not at the enclosing
-- decl head. The rejection fires deep inside `many (appArg …)`, which swallows a
-- recoverable parse failure and leaves the leftover-token path to report a
-- generic "unexpected INT" at the wrong spot; the parser's PFatal (committed)
-- channel is what carries this message and this location out intact.
main = println 4611686018427387904
